translated: Lindwall, Gustaf Alfred Casimir, former district magistrate, Växjö, born 17/12/77 in Valdemarsvik, Östergötland's 1st district, son of retired consul Alfred L. and Beda Reuterskiöld. Married on 10th, to Hedvig af Ekenstam. Children: Ann-Marie, born in 1912, Bachelor of Arts, married to assistant in the penitentiary administration, legal graduate Gunnar Berg; Inga, born in 1913, married to medical licentiate Martin Ekblad; Bo, born in 1915, licentiate of philosophy, art historian; Viveca and Ulf, both born in 1917, Ulf is a legal graduate and court clerk. Bachelor of Arts in Uppsala in 1900, legal international graduate there in 1904. Acting district judge from 1905 to 1907, acting assessor in the Svea Court of Appeal in 1909, adjunct member there in 1910, acting auditor in 1913, assessor in the Svea Court of Appeal in 1915, councillor there in 1917, auditor in 1919, assistant in the financial department in 1922, district magistrate in Växjö from 1924 to 1946. Military judge with the Kronoberg Regiment from 1931 to 1944. Hobbies: literature, languages, sailing. Knight of the Order of the North Star in 1902.
